# Design System Rules

## Typography Hierarchy

### Section Headers (eyebrow labels)
Used for: ABOUT, SELECTED WORK, EXPERTISE, HOW I WORK, CONTACT, CASE STUDY
```
text-[11px] font-medium tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-white/60
md:text-[13px] md:tracking-[0.35em]
mb-4 md:mb-6 lg:mb-8
```

### Page Headings (h1/h2 — serif display)
Used for: hero name, section headings, case study titles, "Let's work together"
```
font-serif font-normal text-white
tracking-[-0.01em] to tracking-[-0.02em]
Use clamp() for responsive sizing
leading-[1.1] to leading-[1.25]
```
Never use `font-light` on serif — Forum only ships weight 400.

### Sub-Headings (h3 — sans utility)
Used for: Growth/Product/Execution titles, Diagnose/Prioritize/Execute/Refine
```
text-lg font-medium tracking-[-0.01em] text-white md:text-xl
```

### Sub-Labels (inside cards/lists)
Used for: Design/Systems/Craft, Before, step numbers, stat labels
```
text-[11px] font-medium tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-white/50
md:text-[12px] md:tracking-[0.3em]
```

### Body Text
```
text-[14px] font-light leading-[1.7] text-gray
md:text-[16px] md:leading-relaxed
```

### Metadata (tags, years, result labels)
```
text-[11px] font-medium tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50
md:text-[12px] md:tracking-[0.25em]
```

### Metrics / Numbers
```
font-medium tabular-nums text-white
```
Sizes vary by context (text-xl in About stats, text-2xl+ in case study results).
Always use `AnimatedMetric` component — never render raw metric strings.

### CTAs / Buttons (uppercase navigation actions)
```
text-[11px] font-medium tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-white/70
md:text-[13px] md:tracking-[0.2em]
```

### Footer Text
```
text-[11px] font-light tracking-[0.12em] text-white/40
md:text-[12px] md:tracking-[0.15em]
```

## Color System

### Prefix/suffix color coding on metrics
- `+` prefix or suffix → `var(--color-success)` (green)
- `−` / `-` prefix or suffix → `var(--color-error)` (red)
- `x` suffix → `var(--color-accent)` (blue)
- `%` and other suffixes → inherit parent color

### Text opacity hierarchy
- `text-white` — headings, primary content
- `text-white/70` — CTAs, interactive elements
- `text-white/60` — section headers, eyebrows
- `text-white/50` — sub-labels, metadata, tags
- `text-white/40` — footer, tertiary info
- `text-gray` (#A1A1A1) — body text

## Spacing System

### Section Padding (all main page sections)
```
pt-12 pb-12 md:pt-16 md:pb-16 lg:pt-20 lg:pb-20
border-t border-white/[0.06]
```
Top and bottom padding are always equal. No `py-*` shorthand — use explicit `pt-` and `pb-` to prevent accidental asymmetry.

### Content Container
All sections wrap content in `.content-grid`:
```
max-width: 1280px, margin: auto, px: 24px
```

### Vertical gaps between elements
Never use `gap-*` on `<main>` — each section owns its own spacing via padding.
Margins between elements within sections should follow the scale: 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 16, 20, 24.

## Font System

### Serif (Forum)
- Used for: hero name, section headings, project titles, case study titles, nav brand mark
- Weight: `font-normal` only (400 is the only available weight)
- Tracking: slightly negative (`-0.01em` to `-0.02em`) on display sizes
- Never use `font-light` with `font-serif`
- Never use `uppercase` with `font-serif`

### Sans (Inter)
- Used for: everything else — body, labels, metadata, CTAs, forms, navigation links
- Weights available: 300 (light), 400 (normal), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold)

## Layout Rules

### Case Studies
`CaseStudyContent` is the single source of truth for case study layout. Both `CaseStudyPage` and `CaseStudyModal` are thin shells that only handle their own chrome (nav vs close bar). Never duplicate case study markup.

### CSS Cascade (Critical)
All custom CSS in `globals.css` must be inside `@layer base` or `@layer components`. Unlayered CSS overrides Tailwind utilities in v4. The `@theme inline` block is the only exception.

### Responsive Breakpoints
- Mobile: default (no prefix)
- Tablet: `md:` (768px)
- Desktop: `lg:` (1024px)
- All components must be mobile-first. Never set mobile values via media queries.

## Accessibility

### Reduced Motion
- Use `MotionConfig reducedMotion="user"` at the app root (already configured in `MotionProvider`)
- For hero-specific animations, check `useReducedMotion()` and skip scroll transforms
- Preloader and CustomCursor are disabled when reduced motion is preferred

### Focus States
- All interactive elements must have `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-white/30`
- Inputs use border-color change instead of outline

### Semantic HTML
- Lists use `<ul>` + `<li>` — no `<div>` inside `<ul>`
- Animated wrappers go inside `<li>`, not replacing it
- Mobile nav overlay uses `role="dialog" aria-modal="true"`
